# State Reset on Route Param Change

When a page uses **dynamic route params** (e.g. `[slug]`, `[id]` in the path like `indoor/[slug]/page.jsx`), **reset all flow and selection state** whenever the param changes. This prevents showing the previous entity’s data or stale UI after navigation.

## Rule

Add a `useEffect` that depends on the resolved param (e.g. `slug`, `id`). When it changes, reset:

- Result/entity state (e.g. `finalProduct`, `selectedItem`)
- List/options state (e.g. `products`, `items`)
- Step/filter/selection state (e.g. `currentStep`, `selectedFilters`, `sensorSelection`)
- `error`
- `isLoading` (set to `false` so a previous fetch doesn’t leave a spinner)

Skip the reset when the param is still empty (e.g. before `params` has resolved): `if (!slug) return`.

## Example

```js
useEffect(() => {
  const resolveParams = async () => {
    const resolved = await params
    setSlug(resolved.slug)
  }
  resolveParams()
}, [params])

// Reset flow state when slug changes (e.g. navigating to another product).
useEffect(() => {
  if (!slug) return
  setFinalProduct(null)
  setProducts([])
  setSensorSelection(null)
  setSelectedFilters({})
  setCurrentStep(0)
  setError(null)
  setIsLoading(false)
}, [slug])
```

## When to Apply

- New `[param]` pages: add this pattern from the start.
- Existing dynamic-route pages: add the reset `useEffect` if you see wrong or stale data after changing the param in the URL.
